Glenognatha gaujoni

(

Figs. 8 
A
–B

) builds its webs a few centimeters (
1–7cm
) above streams in Amazonian rainforests (
Figs. 7C–D
). The web is horizontal with closed hub, few radii and sticky spiral turns (
